<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1293897" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Taraba-state.png?resize=500%2C474&#038;ssl=1" alt="Taraba electoral Commission fixes May 16 for LG polls" width="500" height="474" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Taraba-state.png?w=675&amp;ssl=1 675w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Taraba-state.png?resize=300%2C284&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Taraba-state.png?resize=58%2C55&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Taraba-state.png?resize=205%2C194&amp;ssl=1 205w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Taraba-state.png?resize=137%2C130&amp;ssl=1 137w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Taraba-state.png?resize=560%2C531&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Taraba Independent Electoral Commission (SIEC), on Monday, fixed Saturday, May 16 for the Conduct of Local Government elections. Dr. Philip Duwe, the Chairman of the Commission disclosed this to newsmen in Jalingo on Monday. According to him, the election was supposed to be conducted in 2019 but  could not hold owing to security   challenges in the state. Duwe explained that the budget for the conduct of the polls was approved since 2019. “Today, Feb. 10 the commission wishes to announce the commencement of the process for the conduct of the local government elections into the 16 councils and 168 council wards in the state. “The process will go on within the minimum 90 days’ notice as required by law and elections will be conducted by May 16,”  he said. Duwe appealed to political parties and politicians to play by the rules so as to pave way for peaceful elections. News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the tenure of office of the Executive Chairmen in the state expired several months ago and that Caretaker Committee chairmen are currently holding the offices. vanguard The Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, has won all the 15 local government chairmanship election conducted on Saturday in Taraba State. February 28, 2017 In "News" Four persons living with disabilities have emerged as winners for councillorship poll in the upcoming local government and ward primary elections conducted by the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Taraba. December 14, 2016 In "News" The Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC has trained its staff on Election Monitoring and Support, EMS in Taraba state. December 20, 2018 In "News"